related_questions.question: How much chocolate is OK for you?
related_questions.snippet: The recommended “dose” is approximately 1 to 2 ounces or 30-60g, experts say. Indulge in anything more than that, and you may be consuming too many calories. A 1.45-ounce (41 gram) Hershey's Special Dark Chocolate Bar has 190 calories.

related_questions.question: Why is it called chocolate?
related_questions.snippet: The Mayans called the drink “chocolhaa” (“bitter water”) and Aztecs called it “Xocolatl.” From those words eventually evolved the word “chocolate.” Cacao was used in special celebrations such as those for funeral rituals, war, or harvests.

buttons.subtitle: Why Is Chocolate So Good?
buttons.title: Why chocolate feels so good? It's down to lubrication
buttons.snippet: When chocolate is in contact with the tongue, it releases a fatty film that coats the tongue and other surfaces in the mouth. It is this fatty film that makes the chocolate feel smooth throughout the entire time it is in the mouth.
